<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Crankcase, Crankshaft, and Camshaft -
        Cleaning and Inspection - Crankshaft and Main Bearings
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="1">
        <title>Crankshaft and Main Bearings</title>
        <para>Perform the following steps:</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean the bearing inserts and caps thoroughly in solvent and dry with filtered
                <hotlnk xrefid="safety10" appearance="hottext">compressed air</hotlnk>.
                <emph type="bold">Do not scrape gum or varnish deposits from bearing shells</emph>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean all the internal oil passages of the crankshaft using a
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_205.xml" xrefid="t2650904" appearance="hottext">stiff nylon brush</hotlnk>.
                Loosen all dirt, sludge and deposits which may have accumulated. Flush the oil passages with a suitable
                non-caustic solvent.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Blow passages dry with filtered
                <hotlnk xrefid="safety10" appearance="hottext">compressed air</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the crankshaft journals (main and rod) for scratches, grooves and scoring. Use dye
                penetrant methods to check for cracks.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect all bearing inserts. Replace bearings that are scored, chipped or worn.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650916" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5223.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Inspecting the crankshaft journals</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure the diameter of each journal using a micrometer. Measure each journal at two points,
                right angles to each other. Move the micrometer over the entire width of the journal.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If journals exceed maximum out-of-round specification, crankshaft must be reground or replaced.
                    The crankshaft can be ground to the following undersizes:
                </para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>0.25 mm (0.010 in)</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>0.51 mm (0.020 in)</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>0.76 mm (0.030 in)</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </note>
        </specpara>
